  "name": "Cloak of Feathers",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/commodities/biological/wing-bird-white.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You have learned to blend in with wingless humanoids, and as long as you are not flying, you can fold your wings in a manner that resembles a cloak or robe.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Cha 13, strix.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>When you fold your wings, you gain a +2 bonus on Disguise checks to pose as a human, and ignore the penalties for disguising yourself as a different race while doing so. Additionally, you can hide one small item within your wings' folds (such as a potion, a wand, a weapon weighing 1 pound or less, or a similarly sized item at your GM's discretion). Any such hidden item requires a successful DC 25 Perception check for others to notice. You can retrieve this item with a swift action, but unfolding your wings causes it to drop to the ground.<br/><br/><b>Special</b><br/>Other creatures with natural wings can also take Cloak of Feathers at the GM's discretion, ignoring the racial prerequisite",
